msgstr "Monks’ Confession 47"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "47. Mahānāmasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on Mahānāma"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.47.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.47.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.368"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa964"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country at Kapilavatthu in "
"the Banyan Tree Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena mahānāmassa sakkassa bhesajjaṃ ussannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "At that time Mahānāma the Sakyan had an abundance of medicine."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid "Atha kho mahānāmo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

#. VAR: catumāsaṃ → cātumāsaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ catumāsaṃ bhesajjena pavāretun”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable Sir, I wish to invite the Order to ask for medicines from me for "
"four months.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, mahānāma."
msgstr "“Good, good, Mahānāma."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid "Tena hi tvaṃ, mahānāma, saṃghaṃ catumāsaṃ bhesajjena pavārehī”ti."
msgstr "Please do so.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti."
msgstr "But the monks were afraid of wrongdoing and did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, catumāsaṃ bhesajjappaccayapavāraṇaṃ sāditun”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to accept an invitation to supply medicines for four "
"months.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.47.1.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa965"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ parittaṃ bhesajjaṃ "
"viññāpenti."
msgstr "Yet the monks only asked Mahānāma for a small amount of medicine,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "Tatheva mahānāmassa sakkassa bhesajjaṃ ussannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "and so he still had an abundance."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho mahānāmo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "A second time he went to the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid ""
"“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ aparampi catumāsaṃ bhesajjena pavāretun”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable Sir, I wish to invite the Order to ask for medicines from me for "
"a further four months.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, mahānāma."
msgstr "“Good, good, Mahānāma."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid ""
"Tena hi tvaṃ, mahānāma, saṃghaṃ aparampi catumāsaṃ bhesajjena pavārehī”ti."
msgstr "Please do so.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.369"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti."
msgstr "Again the monks were afraid of wrongdoing and did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, puna pavāraṇampi sāditun”ti."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to accept a further invitation.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.102"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.47.1.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa966"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ parittaṃyeva bhesajjaṃ "
"viññāpenti."
msgstr ""
"Once again the monks only asked Mahānāma for a small amount of medicines,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.2"
msgid "Tatheva mahānāmassa sakkassa bhesajjaṃ ussannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "and so he still had an abundance."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.3"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho mahānāmo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "A third time he  went to the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.6"
msgid "“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ yāvajīvaṃ bhesajjena pavāretun”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable Sir, I wish to invite the Order to ask for medicines from me for "
"life.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.7"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, mahānāma."
msgstr "“Good, good, Mahānāma."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.8"
msgid "Tena hi tvaṃ, mahānāma, saṃghaṃ yāvajīvaṃ bhesajjena pavārehī”ti."
msgstr "Please do so.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.9"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti."
msgstr "Yet again the monks were afraid of wrongdoing and did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.10"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.3.11"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, niccapavāraṇampi sāditun”ti."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to accept a permanent invitation.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.47.1.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa967"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dunnivatthā honti duppārutā "
"anākappasampannā."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six were shabbily dressed and "
"improper in appearance."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.2"
msgid "Mahānāmo sakko vattā hoti—"
msgstr "And Mahānāma criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.3"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, bhante, dunnivatthā duppārutā anākappasampannā?"
msgstr "“Venerables, why are you shabbily dressed and improper in appearance?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.4"
msgid ""
"Nanu nāma pabbajitena sunivatthena bhavitabbaṃ supārutena "
"ākappasampannenā”ti?"
msgstr "Shouldn’t one gone forth be suitably dressed and proper in appearance?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.5"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mahānāme sakke upanandhiṃsu."
msgstr "The monks from the group of six developed a grudge against Mahānāma."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.370"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—“kena nu kho mayaṃ upāyena "
"mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ maṅkuṃ kareyyāmā”ti?"
msgstr "Thinking of ways to humiliate him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.7"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—"
msgstr "it occurred to them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.8"
msgid "“mahānāmena kho, āvuso, sakkena saṃgho bhesajjena pavārito."
msgstr "“Mahānāma has invited the Order to ask for medicines."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.9"
msgid "Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ sappiṃ viññāpemā”ti."
msgstr "Let’s ask him for ghee.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.10"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū yena mahānāmo sakko tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "They then went to Mahānāma"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.11"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

#. One <i lang="pi">doṇa</i> measure of ghee. According ACMC, p.18, one <i lang="pi">doṇa</i> is equivalent to 64 handfuls. It may well be that this amounts to more than one liter, but given the uncertainty one liter seems like a suitably round number.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.12"
msgid "“doṇena, āvuso, sappinā attho”ti."
msgstr "“We need a liter of ghee.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.13"
msgid "“Ajjaṇho, bhante, āgametha."
msgstr "“Venerables, please wait until tomorrow."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.14"
msgid "Manussā vajaṃ gatā sappiṃ āharituṃ."
msgstr "People have gone to the cow-pen to get ghee."

#. VAR: Kālaṃ āharissathā”ti → kālaṃ harissathāti (bj, pts1) | kāle harissathāti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.15"
msgid "Kālaṃ āharissathā”ti."
msgstr "You may come and get it tomorrow morning.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa968"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.16"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe …"
msgstr "A second time"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.17"
msgid ""
"tatiyampi kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ etadavocuṃ—“doṇena, "
"āvuso, sappinā attho”ti."
msgstr "and a third time the monks from the group of six said the same thing,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.18"
msgid "“Ajjaṇho, bhante, āgametha."
msgstr "and Mahānāma replied as before."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.19"
msgid "Manussā vajaṃ gatā sappiṃ āharituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.20"
msgid "Kālaṃ āharissathā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.21"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ pana tayā, āvuso, adātukāmena pavāritena, yaṃ tvaṃ pavāretvā na desī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They then said, “Why do you give an invitation if you don’t wish to give?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.22"
msgid "Atha kho mahānāmo sakko ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "Mahānāma complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.23"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma bhadantā—‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamethā’ti vuccamānā "
"nāgamessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can they not wait for one day when asked?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa969"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.24"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū mahānāmassa sakkassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa "
"vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of Mahānāma,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.25"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.26"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.27"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mahānāmena sakkena—‘ajjaṇho, bhante, "
"āgamethā’ti vuccamānā nāgamessantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six not wait for one day when asked by "
"Mahānāma?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.28"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, mahānāmena sakkena—‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamethā’"
"ti vuccamānā nāgamethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you acted like this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.29"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.30"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.31"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, mahānāmena sakkena—“ajjaṇho, bhante, "
"āgamethā”ti vuccamānā nāgamessatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you not wait for one day when asked by Mahānāma?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.32"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.33"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.33a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.103"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa970"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.371"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
#. VAR: catumāsappaccayapavāraṇā → cātumā­sapaccaya ... (s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.34"
msgid ""
"“Agilānena bhikkhunā catumāsappaccayapavāraṇā sāditabbā, aññatra "
"punapavāraṇāya, aññatra niccapavāraṇāya; tato ce uttari sādiyeyya, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘A monk who is not sick may accept an invitation to ask for requisites for "
"four months. If he accepts one beyond that limit, unless it is a further "
"invitation or a permanent invitation, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.’”"

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs1.4.35"
msgid "(<em>47</em>:<strong>96</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.47.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.47.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa971"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Agilānena bhikkhunā catumāsappaccayapavāraṇā sāditabbāti"
msgstr ""
"A monk who is not sick may accept an invitation to ask for requisites for "
"four months:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "gilānappaccayapavāraṇā sāditabbā."
msgstr "he may accept an invitation to ask for requisites for the sick."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa972"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "Punapavāraṇāpi sāditabbāti"
msgstr "He may accept a further invitation:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "yadā gilāno bhavissāmi tadā viññāpessāmīti."
msgstr "he should think, “When I’m sick, then I’ll ask.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa973"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Niccapavāraṇāpi sāditabbāti"
msgstr "He may accept a permanent invitation:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "yadā gilāno bhavissāmi tadā viññāpessāmīti."
msgstr "he should think, “When I’m sick, then I’ll ask.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa974"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Tato ce uttari sādiyeyyāti"
msgstr "If he accepts one beyond that limit:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "atthi pavāraṇā bhesajjapariyantā na rattipariyantā,"
msgstr ""
"there are invitations that have a limit on the medicines, but no limit on "
"the time period;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "atthi pavāraṇā rattipariyantā na bhesajjapariyantā,"
msgstr ""
"there are invitations that have a limit on the time period, but no limit on "
"the medicines;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "atthi pavāraṇā bhesajjapariyantā ca rattipariyantā ca,"
msgstr ""
"there are invitations that have a limit on both the medicines and the time "
"period;"

#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa975"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "atthi pavāraṇā neva bhesajjapariyantā na rattipariyantā."
msgstr ""
"there are invitations that neither have a limit on the medicines nor on the "
"time period."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Bhesajjapariyantā nāma"
msgstr "Limit on the medicines:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "bhesajjāni pariggahitāni honti—"
msgstr "the medicines are restricted:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "“ettakehi bhesajjehi pavāremī”ti."
msgstr "“I invite you to ask for these particular medicines.”"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Rattipariyantā nāma"
msgstr "Limit on the time period:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "rattiyo pariggahitāyo honti—"
msgstr "the time period is restricted:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "“ettakāsu rattīsu pavāremī”ti."
msgstr "“I invite you to ask during this particular period of time.”"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "Bhesajjapariyantā ca rattipariyantā ca nāma"
msgstr "Limit on both the medicines and the time period:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "bhesajjāni ca pariggahitāni honti rattiyo ca pariggahitāyo honti—"
msgstr "both the medicines and the time period are restricted:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "“ettakehi bhesajjehi ettakāsu rattīsu pavāremī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I invite you to ask for these particular medicines during this particular "
"period of time.”"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "Neva bhesajjapariyantā na rattipariyantā nāma"
msgstr "Neither a limit on the medicines nor on the time period:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.372"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid "bhesajjāni ca apariggahitāni honti rattiyo ca apariggahitāyo honti."
msgstr "neither the medicines nor the time period is restricted."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa976"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid ""
"Bhesajjapariyante—yehi bhesajjehi pavārito hoti tāni bhesajjāni ṭhapetvā "
"aññāni bhesajjāni viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"When there is a limit on the medicines, if he asks for medicines other than "
"those he has been invited to ask for, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.24"
msgid ""
"Rattipariyante—yāsu rattīsu pavārito hoti, tā rattiyo ṭhapetvā aññāsu "
"rattīsu viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"When there is a limit on the period of time, if he asks outside of the "
"period during which he has been invited to ask, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.25"
msgid ""
"Bhesajjapariyante ca rattipariyante ca—yehi bhesajjehi pavārito hoti, tāni "
"bhesajjāni ṭhapetvā yāsu rattīsu pavārito hoti, tā rattiyo ṭhapetvā aññāni "
"bhesajjāni aññāsu rattīsu viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"When there is a limit on both the medicines and on the period of time, if he "
"asks for medicines other than those he has been invited to ask for and he "
"asks outside of the period during which he has been invited to ask, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.1.26"
msgid "Neva bhesajjapariyante na rattipariyante, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"When there is a limit neither on the medicines nor on the period of time, "
"there is no offense."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.47.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa977"></a>
#. VAR: Na bhesajjena karaṇīyena → na bhesajjena karaṇīye (bj, s1-3) | na ­bhesaj­ja­karaṇī­yena (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Na bhesajjena karaṇīyena bhesajjaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he asks for medicine when he has no need for medicine, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid ""
"Aññena bhesajjena karaṇīyena aññaṃ bhesajjaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he asks for a medicine other than the medicine he needs, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.2.2a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Tatuttari tatuttarisaññī bhesajjaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is beyond the limit, and he perceives it as beyond the limit, and he "
"asks for medicine, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Tatuttari vematiko bhesajjaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is beyond the limit, but he is unsure if it is, and he asks for "
"medicine, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Tatuttari natatuttarisaññī bhesajjaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is beyond the limit, but he does not perceive it as beyond the limit, "
"and he asks for medicine, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa978"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Natatuttari tatuttarisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not beyond the limit, but he perceives it as beyond the limit, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Natatuttari vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not beyond the limit, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "Natatuttari natatuttarisaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is not beyond the limit, and he does not perceive it as beyond the "
"limit, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.104"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.47.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa979"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "yehi bhesajjehi pavārito hoti tāni bhesajjāni viññāpeti,"
msgstr "if he asks for those medicines he was invited to ask for;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.373"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "yāsu rattīsu pavārito hoti tāsu rattīsu viññāpeti,"
msgstr "if he asks during the time period that he was invited to ask;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid ""
"“imehi tayā bhesajjehi pavāritāmha, amhākañca iminā ca iminā ca bhesajjena "
"attho”ti ācikkhitvā viññāpeti,"
msgstr ""
" if he asks by informing, “You have invited me to ask for these medicines, "
"but I need such-and-such a medicine;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid ""
"“yāsu tayā rattīsu pavāritāmha tāyo ca rattiyo vītivattā amhākañca "
"bhesajjena attho”ti ācikkhitvā viññāpeti,"
msgstr ""
"if he asks by informing, “The time period during which you invited me to ask "
"has passed, but I need medicine;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ"
msgstr "if it is from relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if it is for the benefit of someone else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.9"
msgid "attano dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.10"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.11"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa980"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc47:pts-cs2.3.12"
msgid "Mahānāmasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr "The seventh rule, the training rule on Mahānāma, is finished."

